                <h1>Discover the Fascinating History of the Leaning Tower of Pisa</h1>
                <p>The Leaning Tower of Pisa, built between the 12th and 14th centuries, is famous for its unintended tilt due to unstable foundation soil. Designed as a freestanding bell tower for the cathedral, its construction faced numerous delays. The iconic structure is now a UNESCO World Heritage site, symbolizing Italy’s architectural ingenuity and resilience.</p>
